<div class="container">
	<div class="text-center my-4">
		<h1 class="fw-light">
			<span class="me-2">How to use</span>
			<span class="display-4 textAqua ">fleet manager</span>
		</h1>
	</div>
	<!-- First window -->
	<div class="myFrame d-flex  flex-column flex-lg-row mb-5 ">
		<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 my-3">
			<h3>Explore the App Without Registration</h3>
			<p class="me-4">
				This demo lets you explore all app features using a pre-filled test account.
				Log in quickly without registration and try viewing, adding, or editing records,
				sorting data, and navigating the full interface — just like a real user.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="myFrame col-12 col-lg-6 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-items-center my-3">
			<h5>No Sign-Up Needed</h5>
			<p class="text-center mt-2 px-3">
				The demo account is temporary — any changes you make will be reset automatically each time you log in again. Feel free to explore without worry!
			</p>
			<form method="post" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="LoginAsDemo" class="mt-3">
				<input type="hidden" name="DemoUser" value="true" />
				<button type="submit" class="btn btn-gradient btn-200w btn-aqua">
					Try Demo
				</button>
			</form>
		</div>
	</div>


	<!-- Second window -->
	<div class="myFrame d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row mb-5">

		<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 d-flex myFrame flex-column gap-2 my-3 me-3 ">
			<h5>Have you not sign up yet?</h5>
			<div class="d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row justify-content-around border-bottom pb-4">
				<div class="d-flex flex-column align-items-center">
					<p>Are you new here?</p>
					<a class="btn btn-gradient btn-200w btn-aqua" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Register">Register</a>
				</div>
				<div class="d-flex flex-column align-items-center ">
					<p>Already have an account?</p>
					<a class="btn btn-gradient btn-200w" asp-controller="Account" asp-action="Login">Log in</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row justify-content-between mt-3 ">
				<div class="me-3">
					<h5>Edit your login data</h5>
					<p>Just click edit button</p>
				</div>				
				<div>
					<img src="/images/small1.png" alt="car-fleet" class="myFrame d-none d-sm-block img-small" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="col-12 col-lg-6 my-3">
			<h3>Register and Manage Your Profile</h3>
			<p>
				To start managing your vehicles, you need to create an account. After successful registration,
				log in with your credentials to access your private dashboard.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Secure registration and login</li>
				<li>Your data is private – only you can see it</li>
				<li>You can change your username or password anytime</li>
			</ul>
			<h5 class="mt-4">Manage Your Profile</h5>
			<p>
				In the profile section, you can update your username and password securely. Your account is protected and only you have access to your data.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Change your username</li>
				<li>Update your password</li>
				<li>Stay in control of your data</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

	</div>

	<!-- Third window -->
	<div class="myFrame d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row mb-5">
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 my-3 me-3">
			<h3>Add and Manage Vehicles</h3>
			<p>
				After logging in, go to the <strong>Your Fleet</strong> section to add your vehicles. You can enter brand, model,
				year, license plate, mileage, and more. You can edit or delete vehicles anytime.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Add multiple vehicles</li>
				<li>Edit or remove existing vehicles</li>
				<li>Search and sort your vehicle list</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 my-3">
			<img src="/images/info1.png" alt="car-fleet" class="d-none d-xxl-block myFrame" />
		</div>
	</div>

	<!-- Fourth window -->
	<div class="myFrame d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row mb-5">
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 me-3 my-3">
			<img src="/images/info2.png" alt="car-fleet" class="d-none d-xxl-block myFrame" />
		</div>
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 my-3">

			<h3>Add Trips and Repairs</h3>
			<p>
				Each vehicle in your fleet has its own detail page where you can manage its records. After adding a car,
				simply <strong>click on its row in the vehicle table</strong> to open the detail view. From there, you can start logging
				trips and repairs:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Trips</strong> – Add a new trip whenever the vehicle is used. Record the start and end date,
					distance traveled, and trip purpose.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Repairs</strong> – Log every maintenance event or repair. Include dates, description,
					mileage at the time of repair, and the cost.
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Tracking this data regularly helps you monitor vehicle usage and service needs, and gives you a full history
				of each car’s lifecycle.
			</p>
			<p>
				All trip logs and repairs are visible and manageable directly from the vehicle’s page, so you always
				know what’s happening with your fleet.
			</p>
		</div>

	</div>

	<!-- Fifth window -->
	<div class="myFrame d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row mb-5">
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 my-3 me-3">
			<h3>Track Your Trips</h3>
			<p>
				For each vehicle, you can log trips, including route details, dates, and distance traveled. This helps
				you track usage and plan maintenance.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Log trip date, route, distance, and purpose</li>
				<li>Review trip history per vehicle</li>
				<li>Access statistics: total km, longest trip, etc.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 my-3">
			<img src="/images/info3.png" alt="car-fleet" class="d-none d-xxl-block myFrame" />
		</div>
	</div>

	<!-- Sixth window -->
	<div class="myFrame d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row mb-5">
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 my-3 me-3">
			<img src="/images/info4.png" alt="car-fleet" class="d-none d-xxl-block myFrame" />
		</div>
		<div class="col-12 col-xl-6 my-3">
			<h3>Log and Track Repairs</h3>
			<p>
				Keep track of vehicle maintenance by logging repairs and service history. Record start and end dates,
				description, mileage at repair, and total cost — so you always know what was done and when.
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Log repair date, description, and duration</li>
				<li>Track cost and mileage at time of repair</li>
				<li>View full repair history for each vehicle</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
